This project supports various operations required to perform CCA.


____________________________________________________________________
1. When you have a raw text corpus (tokenized!)

(a) Derive n-gram counts from the corpus:

python cca.py --corpus input/example/example.corpus

(b) Cutoff rare words in the n-grams (you need unigram counts):

python cca.py --ngrams input/example/example.3grams --cutoff 1 --unigrams input/example/example.1grams

(c) Extract features from this processed n-gram counts:

python cca.py --ngrams input/example/example.3grams.cutoff1 --extract_views

(d) Run CCA on this feature file:

python cca.py --views input/example/example.3grams.cutoff1.featurized 

You can specify the parameters

  --cca_dim CCA_DIM     number of CCA dimensions
  --extra_dim EXTRA_DIM
                        oversampling parameter
  --power_num POWER_NUM
                        number of power iterations
  --kappa KAPPA         pseudocounts for smoothing
  --wantB               write view 2 projeciton as well?

(e) Examine the output:

output/example.3grams.cutoff1.featurized.cca_dim200.kappa100.extra_dim40.power_num5.out/A
output/example.3grams.cutoff1.featurized.cca_dim200.kappa100.extra_dim40.power_num5.out/corr


____________________________________________________________________
2. When you have a processed n-gram file (e.g., from Google n-grams)

Start from step (c).

